  "texts": [
    "Finsterle is a senior scientist and the head of the World Standard Group (WSG) at PMOD/WRC.",
    "He has more than 30 years of experience in radiometry.",
    "He is the PI of the PMO6 radiometer on board of the SOHO/VIRGO mission, the PI of the DARA instrument on the FY3E/JTSIM mission, the PI of the CLARA/NORSAT-1 absolute radiometer and the co-PI of the DARA-PROBA3 radiometer on the ESA-PROBA3 satellite (expected to be launched later in 2024).",
    "His main research focuses on the estimation of total solar irradiance, the Earth energy imbalance, and the Earth radiation budget.",
    "He is involved in the application of machine learning in dealing with automatic correction of observations due to the degradation of instruments in space from long exposure to UV/EUV."
  ],
